  "prompt": "How much does it cost to complete undergraduation in Purdue University as an International student?",
  "response": "The cost of undergraduate attendance at Purdue University as an international student can be broken down into several categories:\n\n**1. Tuition and Fees:**\n\n*   This is the biggest expense. As of the most recent estimates (for the 2023-2024 academic year), **annual tuition and fees for international undergraduate students are roughly $31,142**.  Keep in mind that tuition and fees typically increase slightly each year. It's always best to check the official Purdue University Bursar's Office website for the most up-to-date figures.\n\n**2. Living Expenses:**\n\n*   **Housing and Food:** This includes on-campus dorms, meal plans, or off-campus apartments and groceries. Purdue estimates this to be around **$13,458 per year**.\n*   **Books and Supplies:** Expect to spend around **$840 per year** on textbooks, course materials, and other academic supplies.\n*   **Personal Expenses:** This covers items like clothing, entertainment, and personal care. Purdue estimates this at **$2,900 per year**.\n*   **Transportation:**  This includes local transportation (bus, car, etc.) and potentially travel expenses to/from home country.  Purdue estimates **$1,200 per year**.\n\n**3. Health Insurance:**\n\n*   Purdue requires all international students to have health insurance.  The cost is approximately **$2,600 per year**.\n\n**4. Visa Fees and SEVIS Fee:**\n\n*   These are one-time fees associated with obtaining and maintaining your student visa. The SEVIS fee is paid before your visa interview.  These are generally a few hundred dollars total.\n\n**5. Other Potential Costs:**\n\n*   **Application Fees:** When applying to Purdue.\n*   **Orientation Fees:** Fees associated with international student orientation.\n\n**Total Estimated Cost:**\n\nAdding these up, a conservative estimate for the **total annual cost** of attending Purdue University as an international undergraduate student is approximately:\n\n$31,142 (Tuition & Fees) + $13,458 (Housing & Food) + $840 (Books) + $2,900 (Personal) + $1,200 (Transport) + $2,600 (Health Insurance)  = **Approximately $52,140 per year.**\n\n**Therefore, for a four-year degree, the estimated total cost would be around $208,560** (This is a *very* rough estimate, as costs can change and are highly dependent on lifestyle choices).\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **This is just an estimate.** Your actual expenses may vary depending on your lifestyle, spending habits, and chosen living arrangements.\n*   **Tuition increases:** Tuition rates are subject to change each year. Always check the Bursar's Office website for the latest rates.\n*   **Currency Fluctuations:** Exchange rates can impact the actual cost in your home currency.\n*   **Financial Aid:** International students are generally not eligible for federal financial aid (FAFSA).  However, Purdue offers some merit-based scholarships and departmental scholarships for international students. Research and apply for these opportunities.\n*   **Cost-Saving Strategies:** Consider living off-campus, buying used textbooks, and being mindful of your spending habits to reduce costs.\n* **University Website:** Check Purdue's official website for the most current and accurate information.  Specifically look for the \"Cost of Attendance\" or \"Tuition and Fees\" sections on the Bursar's Office or International Student Services websites.\n\n**Where to Find the Most Accurate Information:**\n\n*   **Purdue University Bursar's Office:**  This is the primary source for tuition and fee information.  Look for the \"Cost of Attendance\" section.\n*   **Purdue University International Student and Scholar Services (ISSS):**  ISSS provides information and support for international students, including estimated costs of living.\n*   **Specific Program Websites:**  Some academic programs may have additional fees or required materials that are not included in the general cost estimates.\n\nBy consulting these official sources, you can obtain the most accurate and up-to-date information for planning your educational finances at Purdue University. Good luck!\n",
